author: cbs8
title: Fisherman drowns at wildlife refuge near Natchez
text:
NATCHEZ, Miss. (AP) - Authorities say the body of an 86-year-old man has been recovered from Gilliard Lake on the St. Catherine Creek National Wildlife Refuge in south Adams County.
A sheriff's office spokesman tells The Natchez Democrat ( http://bit.ly/1VUiAJt ) the body of Frank Sullivan was recovered Tuesday evening by the sheriff's deputies and members of Adams County Search and Rescue.
Coroner James Lee said the cause of death has been determined to be drowning.
Information from: The Natchez Democrat, http://www.natchezdemocrat.com/
